While editing any configuration, clicking cancel leads to this error:
{code}
{"error":{"message":"Token not found","code":"AUTHENTICATION_FAILED"}}
{code}

# Open a project and click on "Slack integration";
# Click Edit on any of the existing connections;
# Click Cancel to return to the list of connections;
# Appears the error;
# Refresh browser - connection list page finally loads;

Add a {{jira-cloud-for-outlook}} label or "Issue created from Jira Cloud for Outlook" to the description when the issue was created or email was sent to issue from Outlook. This is for [more insights or reporting purposes|https://community.atlassian.com/t5/Jira-Software-questions/Filtering-issues-in-Jira-cloud-that-were-created-using-Outlook/qaq-p/1484533].
h3. Workaround

This JQL will show issues with attached emails but won't show issues that were created from Jira Cloud for Outlook add-in and without the "Include email" checkbox ticked.

{code:java}
issue.property["atlassian-outlook-integration"].hasAttachedEmails > 0
{code}
